// Adversarial: High action_prob (0.8) chaos drives the breaker across the Dense
// layout at near-maximum velocity, maximising the chance of the breaker body
// overlapping a cell during a frame — the BreakerImpactCell dispatch path.
// This path is less exercised than BoltImpactCell; bugs in the breaker-side
// impact bridge (double dispatch, missing message filter, wrong target routing)
// tend to surface only when the breaker physically crosses a cell boundary at
// speed. Dense layout packs cells to the edges so the breaker reaches them on
// any leftward or rightward dash from the default centre spawn.
// If BreakerImpactCell fires multiple times for a single contact (duplicate event),
// NoEntityLeaks catches orphaned effect or impact entities that didn't clean up.
// BreakerInBounds guards against a velocity-integration bug flinging the breaker
// outside the playfield after a cell impact impulse.
// BoltInBounds and NoNaN cover downstream bolt physics corruption from the same
// impact event chain.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.8)),
    max_frames: 3000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 1301,
)
